In determining whether a program or service encourages and promotes the efficient use and conservation of energy, the Commission shall consider the:
cost-effectiveness;
impact on rates of each ratepayer class;
impact on jobs; and
impact on the environment.

Incentives may include:
time-of-day pricing of electricity;
credits on distribution charges;
rebates on the cost of charging systems;
demand response programs; or
other incentives approved by the Commission.
